      <abstract>
        <p>Cambodian Prime Min Hun Sen orders homes of Pol Pot and other former Khmer Rouge leaders, Anlong Veng, preserved as tourist attractions (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Prime Minister Hun Sen has ordered that the homes of Pol Pot and other former leaders of the Khmer Rouge be preserved as tourist attractions. The homes are in the dusty town of Anlong Veng, a three-hour drive from the ancient temples of Angkor, which draw hundreds of thousands of visitors each year.</p>
        <p>Seth Mydans (NYT)</p>
      </block>
